        <page n="02" image="va.au.rv.1863.03.06">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Impressment of Supplies</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The editor responds to an editorial from the Spectator, which stated that
                    farmers would not grow more than their families needed unless they had some
                    guarantee against or compensation for impressment of their harvest. The editor
                    of the Vindicator asserts that farmers of the Confederacy will continue to raise
                    whatever is necessary for the army out of patriotism, not because of
                    legislation.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look>**</look>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Conscription in the North</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"Let us then do all that we can to add to the comfort and efficiency of our
                    brave men in arms, and prepare to meet, at every point, these myrmidons of the
                    Tyrannical Dictator, with invincible forces."</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>This editorial cites new conscription efforts in the North that may raise
                    the number of troops to one million. This number should not intimidate the
                    Southern troops, however, which already "have had to meet great odds in every
                    conflict."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look>**</look>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Concerts</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The cornet band of the 5th Virginia Infantry performed concerts last
                    Tuesday and Wednesday for large audiences. The proceeds from Tuesday's concert
                    will benefit the soldiers; those from Wednesday will benefit soldiers' wives and
                    children in Staunton. The total amount raised was nearly $600.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Artificial Leg</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
